Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.30,0:00:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是我們的搖籃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yes, this is home.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.20,0:00:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.51,0:00:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,找不到熟悉的大陸嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Having trouble finding a familiar continent?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.44,0:00:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,這是因為過去的地球與現在完全不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The past is another planet. Actually, many.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.38,0:00:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,而在我腳下的 就是宇宙大爆炸以來的所有時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'm standing on the great expanse of time that has elapsed since the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.90,0:00:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,為了更好地理解大爆炸後發生了什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In order to think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.95,0:00:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我們把時間壓縮成1年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we've compressed it all into a single year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.79,0:00:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,現在是宇宙年歷上的12月23號的清晨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's the early morning of December 23 on this Cosmic Calendar of ours,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.63,0:00:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,大約3億5千萬年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or about 350 million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.96,0:00:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,當時我們的世界才剛剛40億歲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when our world was a mere four billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.37,0:00:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,地球看上去完全不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Earth looks so different.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.04,0:00:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你完全認不出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You might not even know the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.97,0:00:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,天上的星星也幫不了你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The stars wouldn't help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.81,0:00:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,當時的星座也和現在的不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even the constellations would have been different back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.08,0:01:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,恐龍要在1億多年後才會出現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The dinosaurs were still more than 100 million years in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.02,0:01:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,那時候也沒有鳥 沒有花\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There were no birds, no flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.92,0:01:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,就連空氣都不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the air was different, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.43,0:01:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,大氣層中的氧氣濃度空前絕後地高\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The atmosphere had more oxygen than at any other time in Earth's history,  before or since.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.10,0:01:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,這使得昆蟲可以長得比現在大得多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This allowed insects to grow much larger than they do today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.27,0:01:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,怎麼會這樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.28,0:01:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,昆蟲沒有肺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Insects don't have lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.94,0:01:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,它們由身體上對外的開口獲得生命必須的氧氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Life-giving oxygen is taken in through openings in the outside of their bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.45,0:01:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,然後通過管道網絡傳遍全身\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and transported through a network of tubes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.95,0:01:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,如果昆蟲長得太大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If an insect were too large,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.95,0:01:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,這些管道的外圍就會吸收盡所有的氧氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the outer reaches of these tubes would absorb all the oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.39,0:01:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,氧氣就無法到達內部的器官\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before it could ever get to its internal organs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.06,0:01:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但是在石炭紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But during the Carboniferous Period,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.06,0:01:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}距今2.9-3.55億年
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.66,0:01:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,大氣層的氧氣濃度是現在的兩倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the atmosphere had almost twice the oxygen as today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.56,0:01:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,昆蟲可以長得很大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Insects could then grow much bigger
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.97,0:01:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,依然可以獲得足夠的氧氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and still get enough oxygen in their bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.63,0:01:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是為什麼 蜻蜓可以和老鷹一樣大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why the dragonflies here are as big as eagles
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.27,0:02:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,千足蟲和鱷魚一樣大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the millipedes the size of alligators.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.34,0:02:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼為什麼那時候會有如此充足的氧氣呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So why was there so much oxygen back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.48,0:02:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,其實它們都由一個全新的生物製造的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was produced by a new kind of life.
