Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.00,0:03:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\N{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第九集
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.91,0:03:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,是什麼樣的生物讓大氣層發生了這麼戲劇化的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What kind of life could've changed the Earth's atmosphere so dramatically?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.55,0:03:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,這些參天的植物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Plants that could reach for the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.56,0:03:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,大樹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.29,0:04:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,在它們為了獲得陽光的競賽中 進化出了抵抗引力的方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In their competition for sunlight, trees evolved a way to defy gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.89,0:04:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,樹出現以前 最高的植物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Before trees, the tallest vegetation was
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.63,0:04:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,只不過高及腰際\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}only about waist-high.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.63,0:04:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,然後奇跡發生了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And then something wonderful happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.61,0:04:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,一個植物分子在強度和彈性方面都獲得了進化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A plant molecule evolved that was both strong and flexible,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.78,0:04:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,這種材料可以支撐很大的重量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a material that could support a lot of weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.98,0:04:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,也可以在風中彎曲而不折斷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}yet bend in the wind without breaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.25,0:04:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,木質素造就了樹的誕生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Lignin made trees possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.65,0:04:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,現在生命可以向上發展\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now life could build upward.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.09,0:04:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,並且打開了一片全新的領域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And this opened a whole new territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.29,0:04:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,這些遠離地面的群體形成一個三維的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a three-dimensional matrix for communities far above the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.29,0:04:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,地球變成了樹的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Earth became the Planet of the Trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.03,0:04:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但是木質素有個缺點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But lignin had a downside
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.20,0:04:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,不易食\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it was hard to swallow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.64,0:04:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,天然拆遷辦成員 真菌和細菌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When nature's demolition crew, the fungi and bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.37,0:04:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,負責消化一切有木質素的物體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}tried to eat anything with lignin in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.71,0:04:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,結果就是嚴重的消化不良\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they got a really bad case of indigestion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.31,0:04:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,白蟻要在至少1億年後才會進化出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And termites wouldn't evolve for at least another 100 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.38,0:04:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,該拿那些死掉的樹怎麼辦呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What to do with all those dead trees?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.72,0:05:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,真菌和細菌花費了幾百萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It took the fungi and bacteria millions of years
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.49,0:05:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,才進化出消化它們的化學方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to evolve the biochemical means to consume them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.72,0:05:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,與此同時 樹不斷地生長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Meanwhile, the trees just kept springing up,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.73,0:05:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,死亡 倒下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}dying, falling over
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.73,0:05:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,再由萬年積累的泥土覆蓋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and getting buried by the mud that built up over eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.20,0:05:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,最終 億萬的樹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Eventually, there were hundreds of billions of trees
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,被深埋地下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}entombed in the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.14,0:05:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,被埋葬在世界各地的森林\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}buried forests all over the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.34,0:05:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,那會帶來什麼潛在的危害呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What possible harm could come from that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.49,0:05:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,新斯科捨省的這個懸崖是另一種年歷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This cliff in Nova Scotia is another kind of calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.99,0:05:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,它訴說著另一個曾經在這裏繁榮世界的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It tells the story of that other world that once flourished right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.83,0:05:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一棵3億年古樹的死亡面具\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And this is the death mask of that 300 million-year-old tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.74,0:05:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,它由礦物打造 礦物替代了原本的木頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was cast by minerals that replaced the original wood
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.24,0:05:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,替代了每一個細胞 它又被稱為 化石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}cell by cell-- in other words, a fossil.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.84,0:06:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,很久以前 樹將它的有機分子擴散到周圍的環境中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The tree surrendered its organic molecules to the environment long ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.05,0:06:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,包括碳元素和水分 只留下它的形狀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its carbon and water. Only its shape remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.68,0:06:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,這棵樹還活著時 它吸入二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When this tree was alive, it took in carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.69,0:06:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,還有水分 利用陽光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and water and used sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.69,0:06:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,把它們轉化成富含能量的有機物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to turn them into energy-rich organic matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.53,0:06:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,然後把氧氣作為廢物排出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The tree gave off oxygen as a waste product.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.53,0:06:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,至今樹和其他植物依然是這樣做的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's what trees and other plants still do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.90,0:06:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,植物死亡後 它們腐爛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When plants die, they decay,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.27,0:06:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,並且反轉那個過程\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and this reverses the transaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.44,0:06:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,它們的有機物與氧氣結合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their organic matter combines with oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.07,0:06:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,然後分解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and decomposes,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.24,0:06:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,將二氧化碳排放到空氣中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}putting carbon dioxide back into the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.65,0:06:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,這使得地球大氣層的化學物質達到平衡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This balances the books for the chemistry of Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.98,0:06:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,如果樹在腐爛前就被埋葬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But if the trees are buried before they can decay,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.42,0:06:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,那會發生兩件事 它們帶著碳元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}two things happen... they take the carbon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.26,0:06:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,並將太陽能儲藏在裏面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and stored solar energy with them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.32,0:06:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,不帶走氧氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and leave the oxygen behind
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.39,0:06:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,任由它在大氣中積累\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to build up in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.33,0:06:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是3億年前的狀況\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's what happened around 300 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.23,0:06:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,當時氧氣過剩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There was an oxygen surplus.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.17,0:06:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,因此蟲子們可以長得如此巨大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's how the bugs got so big.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.24,0:06:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,那些被掩埋的碳又會怎樣呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And what became of all that buried carbon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.24,0:07:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,它們與世隔絕 深埋地下億萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It lay there for eons before dealing life on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.31,0:07:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,然後發生了有史以來最具毀滅性的爆發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its most devastating blow of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.15,0:07:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,在地球上有些地方 你可以跨越時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are places on this planet where you can walk through time
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.29,0:07:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,閱讀岩石中蘊含的歷史\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and read the history written in the rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.92,0:07:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,新斯科捨省的海灘就是這樣的一個地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This beach in Nova Scotia is one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.79,0:07:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,每一層都是一頁書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every layer is a page.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.36,0:07:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,每一層都訴說著一個大洪水的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each one tells the story of a flood,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.63,0:07:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,一個接一個 持續幾百萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one after another, over millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.37,0:07:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,像夾心蛋糕一樣的洪水沉積層 逐漸被掩埋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The layer cake of flood deposits was slowly buried
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.14,0:07:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,在溫度和壓力的作用下 變為岩石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and turned into rock by heat and pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.31,0:07:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,這些同樣的力量產生了山脈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The same forces that built mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.14,0:07:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,連同被埋葬的化石森林一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}then tilted and uplifted them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.81,0:07:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,在它們的基礎上 傾斜再慢慢積高\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}along with the entombed fossil forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.45,0:07:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,新的岩層總是堆積在老的岩層之上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The newer layers were always deposited on top of the older ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.12,0:07:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,就如所有的書頁都按照正確的順序排列\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All the pages are in the correct order,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.82,0:07:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,記錄著幾百萬年來這裏曾經的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}bearing witness to what happened here over millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.69,0:07:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,後面那裏 藏著更古老的過去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Back that way lies the more distant past.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.50,0:07:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我每向前走一步\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And with every step I take,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.46,0:08:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,相當於向現在邁進1千年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I move about 1,000 years closer to the present
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.67,0:08:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,同時遠離那個3億年前的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and away from the world of 300 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.04,0:08:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,那邊就是5千萬年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}50 million years later lies that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.48,0:08:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,這是二疊紀末期的開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was the beginning of the end of the Permian world,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.25,0:08:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是一場無與倫比的大滅絕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an event of unequalled carnage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.26,0:08:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,二疊紀是滅絕紀念堂裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Permian is the darkest corridor
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.09,0:08:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,最沉重的一條走廊 也是紀念生命之樹上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in this memorial to the broken branches on the Tree of Life--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.76,0:08:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,其中的一根斷枝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Halls of Extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.00,0:08:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,2億5千萬年來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Death has never come so close
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.07,0:08:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,死神從沒像這樣般 想要統治整個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to reigning supreme on this world in the quarter billion years since.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.34,0:08:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,在現今西伯利亞發生的火山爆發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The eruptions, in what is now Siberia,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.17,0:08:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,持續了幾十萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}lasted for hundreds of thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.18,0:08:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,熔漿燒燬了上百萬平方英里的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The lava flooded and buried more than a million square miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.58,0:08:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,這次的災難使其他歷史時期的火山爆發相形見絀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This event dwarfs any volcanic eruption in historical times.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.72,0:09:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}滅絕紀念堂
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.21,0:09:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,從火山裂縫中洩出大量的二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Huge quantities of carbon dioxide came pouring out of the volcanic fissures
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.38,0:09:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,這溫室氣體使得大氣溫度不斷攀升\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This greenhouse gas warmed the climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.38,0:09:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,使得早先在石炭紀就被埋葬的森林再次回到我們的故事中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And this is where the long-buried forests of the earlier Carboniferous Period reenter the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.15,0:09:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,在5千萬年的時間裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}During the intervening 50 million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.66,0:09:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,那些樹變成了巨大的煤礦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}those trees had turned into immense deposits of coal,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.33,0:09:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,就因為這樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and as it happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.66,0:09:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,世界上最大儲量的煤礦之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one of the world's largest accumulations of coal
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.06,0:09:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,就被埋在西伯利亞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was buried right there in Siberia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.67,0:09:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,熔岩的溫度烘烤著煤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The heat from the lava baked the coal,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.34,0:09:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,促使沼氣和富硫氣體衝出地表\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}driving methane and sulfur-rich gases out of the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.64,0:09:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,同時滿載著有毒的放射性塵埃微粒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They were laden with toxic and radioactive ash particles
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.94,0:09:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是煤煙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}coal smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.41,0:09:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,這種邪惡的混合物對空氣造成了嚴重的污染\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This witch's brew polluted the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.18,0:10:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,也從根本上導致了地球溫度的失衡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and radically destabilized Earth's climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.45,0:10:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,硫酸霧霾隔絕了陽光 使地球陷入黑暗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A sulfuric acid haze blocked incoming sunlight and darkened the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.09,0:10:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,全球溫度驟降至冰點以下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Global temperatures plummeted to subfreezing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.50,0:10:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,在火山噴發的間歇期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}During lulls in the eruptions,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.10,0:10:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,硫酸霧霾落回地面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the acid haze fell back to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.60,0:10:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但是二氧化碳繼續\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the carbon dioxide remained
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.67,0:10:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在空氣中累積 導致全球變暖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and built up in the atmosphere to cause global warming.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.68,0:10:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,多年的嚴寒與上千年的酷熱交替出現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Years of frigid cold alternating with millennia of stifling heat
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.45,0:10:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,導致了動植物的數量減少\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}battered a dwindling population of plants and animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.12,0:10:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,它們沒有機會去適應劇烈的氣溫變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They had no chance to adapt to the drastic swings in climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.52,0:10:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,隨著全球變暖的持續\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As the global warmingcontinued,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.63,0:10:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,表層和深層的水逐漸混合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the surface and the bottom waters slowly mixed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.76,0:10:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,使曾經冰冷的海床水溫升高\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}raising the temperature of the once-frigid depths of the sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.17,0:10:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,令沉積物中富含沼氣的冰也開始融化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Methane-rich ices that had been frozen in the sediments began to melt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.98,0:11:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,重獲自由的沼氣浮上水面並且進入空氣中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newly liberated methane gas made its way to the surface and into the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.58,0:11:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,而沼氣比二氧化碳能夠更有效地吸收熱量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Methane traps heat far more efficiently than carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.15,0:11:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,於是氣候變得更炎熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so the climate got even hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.09,0:11:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,沼氣也破壞了了平流層中的臭氧層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the methane also destroyed the ozone layer in the stratosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.23,0:11:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,保護生物不受致命紫外線傷害的天然防曬霜 已經被侵蝕了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The natural sunscreen that protects life from deadly ultraviolet rays was eaten away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.93,0:11:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,全球海洋的循環系統停止了工作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The circulatory system of the world ocean shut down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.34,0:11:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,水裏的空氣耗盡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These stagnant waters became oxygen-starved,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.84,0:11:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,殺死了大海中幾乎所有的魚類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}killing almost all the fish in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.24,0:11:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,但有一種生物在這殘酷的環境中得以繁榮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But one kind of life flourished in this brutal environment...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.58,0:11:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,那是能排泄出硫化氫的一種細菌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}bacteria that produced deadly hydrogen sulfide gas as a waste product.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.45,0:11:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,它也是壓死駱駝的最後一根稻草\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That was the last straw.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.36,0:11:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,有毒氣體殺死了陸地上幾乎其他所有的植物和動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The poison gas killed almost all the remaining plants and animals on the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.26,0:11:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是大滅絕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was the Great Dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.43,0:11:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上生命最接近全部滅絕的一次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The closest life on Earth has ever come to annihilation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.44,0:12:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,十分之九的物種不復存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nine in ten of all species perished.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.14,0:12:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,地球花費了很久才使生命重燃生機\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It took a long time for life to bounce back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.74,0:12:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,而這幾百萬年 地球可以用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For a few million years, Earth could have been called
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.28,0:12:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"死氣沉沉"來形容\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Planet of the Dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.15,0:12:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的祖先是少數倖存物種之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We are descended from one of the few species that managed to squeak by
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.42,0:12:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你作為人類 並且現在還能存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You are human and alive at this very moment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.93,0:12:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,都應該歸功於它們將DNA\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because they managed to endure, conveying
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.60,0:12:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,從這生物歷史上最危險的時期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}their DNA through one of the most treacherous periods
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.73,0:12:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,延續下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the history of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.88,0:12:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,這座山脈完全由生物組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This mountain was made entirely by life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.52,0:12:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,在地獄大門大開之前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The life that flourished back in the glory days
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.85,0:12:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,這些生物都曾經在二疊紀有著輝煌的過去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the Permian, before all hell broke loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.19,0:12:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏是長達400英里的瓜達魯普山脈的一部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is part of the 400 mile-long
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.86,0:12:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,貫穿德克薩斯和新墨西哥州\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Guadalupe Mountain chain that runs through Texas and New Mexico
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.09,0:13:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,世界上最大的化石巖礁\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's the world's largest fossil reef.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.50,0:13:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏曾是一大片內陸海\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All this was once a great inland sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.53,0:13:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,這個巖礁欣欣向榮了好幾百年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The reef flourished and grew for millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.90,0:13:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,她曾是海綿生物 綠藻生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and was home to multitudes of sponges, green algae,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.27,0:13:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,還有很多小得看不見的生物賴以為生的家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and animals too small to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.88,0:13:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,這些生物死亡後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When these creatures died,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.88,0:13:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,它們沉到海底 並被淤泥覆蓋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they sank to the bottom and were buried in the silt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.02,0:13:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,幾百萬年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Over millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.22,0:13:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,它們的殘骸變成石油和天然氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}their remains were converted into oil and gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.22,0:13:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,最終 盆地被淤泥填滿 巖礁死亡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Eventually, the basin silted in and the reef died.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.62,0:13:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,然後 這座海底鬼城被深埋在地下一英里處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This marine ghost town was then buried a mile beneath the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.13,0:13:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,後來 構造作用力將骷髏般的巖礁推上海平面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Later, tectonic forces lifted the skeletal reef high above sea level,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.75,0:13:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,於是它又被風雨侵蝕了無數年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where it was eroded and sculpted over eons by wind and rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.57,0:13:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,想像一下這裏2.75億年前的樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just imagine what this place looked like 275 million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.38,0:13:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,那時候的熱帶內陸海有幾座小島在海中漂浮著 海水裏充滿了生氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when it was a vibrant, tropical inland sea, dotted with islands
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.45,0:13:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,生命之火還在那熊熊燃燒著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and brimming with life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.72,0:14:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,而在大約2.2億年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until about 220 million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.32,0:14:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,新英格蘭和北美洲還靠得很近\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}New England and North Africa were next-door neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.39,0:14:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,那時還沒有大西洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There was no such thing as the Atlantic Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.43,0:14:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,中間那些藍色的狹長地帶 還只是湖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those thin blue fingers at the center-- they were lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.77,0:14:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,它們是超大陸分裂的最初顯著標誌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They were the first outward signs that the supercontinent
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.74,0:14:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,同時也預示了地球上的生命將迎來又一次的巨變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was splitting apart and that life on Earth was due for another big shake-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.51,0:14:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,1百萬年後 這些湖變成了一條長長的海灣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A million years later, the lakes became a long bay,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.81,0:14:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,然後逐漸變成大西洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which would grow into the Atlantic Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.75,0:14:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,地表的這些意義重大的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These profound changes at the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.35,0:14:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,卻遠遠無法與地球深處發生的變化相提並論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were merely symptoms of a drama that was unfolding far beneath, in the depths of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.19,0:14:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,人類出現時 這些可以揭示地球劇變的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By the time we got here, the telltale traces
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.09,0:14:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,蛛絲馬跡已被淹沒在大洋深處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of global upheaval were buried at the bottom of the deep blue sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.10,0:14:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我們已經完全不清楚地球殘酷無比的過去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We were completely cut off from the great story of Earth's violent past
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.27,0:14:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,就像失憶癥患者一樣迫切的想要知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a species of amnesiacs trying to find out
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.04,0:14:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他們是誰 以前究竟發生了什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who we were and what happened before we awakened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.01,0:14:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,1570年亞伯拉罕·奧特柳斯繪製了首張\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1570, Abraham Ortelius created the first
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.81,0:15:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,現代世界地圖 都歸功於\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}modern world atlas, reflecting on the discoveries
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.32,0:15:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,過去80年熱衷探索的黃金時代裏的偉大發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the previous 80 years-- the Golden Age of Exploration.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.36,0:15:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,還沒等墨跡乾透\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Before the ink was dry,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.16,0:15:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,奧特柳斯便已經開始仔細審視他的傑作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ortelius stepped back from his masterpiece
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.63,0:15:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,他首先發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and became the first of many to notice the striking
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.00,0:15:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,大西洋兩側的大陸邊緣相互吻合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}puzzle-piece fit between the continent on either side of the Atlantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.70,0:15:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,他隨後寫道 美洲是因為地震和洪水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He later wrote that the Americas were torn away
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.97,0:15:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,才與歐非大陸分離開\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from Europe and Africa by earthquakes and floods.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.04,0:15:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,但是奧特柳斯的觀察結論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Ortelius's observation
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.84,0:15:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,在隨後的幾百年裏 都被認為那只不過是他的直覺而已\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}remained nothing more than a hunch for the next couple of centuries...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.05,0:15:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,直到20世紀早期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}until an early 20th century
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.55,0:15:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,德國的一位天文學家兼氣象學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}German astronomer and meteorologist
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.55,0:15:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,才用積累的證據 使之成為一個科學理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}amassed the evidence to build the scientific case for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.56,0:15:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,第一次世界大戰期間 阿爾弗雷德·魏格納應徵入伍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Alfred Wegener had been drafted during the First World War,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.73,0:15:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,不久就負傷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but was wounded soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.20,0:15:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,在戰地醫院恢復期間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As he recovered in a field hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.53,0:15:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,他從科學文獻中搜尋地球往事的線索\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he scoured scientific literature for clues to the Earth's past.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.40,0:15:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,多年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Years before,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.10,0:16:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,魏格納在大學圖書館裏偶爾讀了一篇有趣的論文\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wegener had happened upon an intriguing paper in the stacks of his university library.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.37,0:16:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,魏格納迷惑了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It puzzled Wegener
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.88,0:16:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,現在已經滅絕的同種蕨類化石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that fossils of the same species of a now-extinct fern
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.35,0:16:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,竟然在大西洋兩岸都有發現它們的報道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were reported to be found on both sides of the Atlantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.02,0:16:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,更令人驚奇的是 同種類的恐龍化石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even more curious were the discoveries of fossils
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.76,0:16:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,也在兩邊的大陸都有發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the same dinosaurs on both continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.96,0:16:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,而在20世紀早期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the early 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.89,0:16:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,地質學家對這種現象做了解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}geologists explained how life crossed the oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.46,0:16:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他們想像兩塊大陸間曾經有一塊陸地連接\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by imagining that land bridges had once existed between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.30,0:16:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,他們相信這些連接的陸地在之前逐漸瓦解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was thought that these land bridges gradually disintegrated
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.77,0:16:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,然後消失在海底了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and vanished beneath the waves long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.07,0:16:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,但是有一個證據使得魏格納相信\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there was one piece of evidence that convinced Wegener
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.61,0:16:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,這個主流的科學觀點肯定錯了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the prevailing scientific view must be wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.91,0:16:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,證據就是地球本身\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Earth itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.55,0:16:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,一條山脈怎麼會跨越海洋的分割\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why would a mountain range cross the oceanic divide
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.12,0:16:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,又在另一塊大陸繼續綿延\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to continue on another continent?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.32,0:16:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼巴西和南非所發現的岩石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And why would you find the same unique pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.46,0:16:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,有著相同的獨特構造規律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the layers of rocks in both Brazil and South Africa?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.13,0:16:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,還有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And another thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.13,0:16:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼熱帶的植物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}under what circumstances could tropical plants have flourished
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.40,0:17:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,居然會出現在北冰洋的冰天雪地中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the frozen wastes of the Arctic?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.80,0:17:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,魏格納推斷只有一種符合邏輯的解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wegener concluded that there was only one logical solution to this puzzle...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.68,0:17:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上曾經有一塊超級大陸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There had once been a single supercontinent on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.15,0:17:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他稱之為 盤古大陸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He named it Pangaea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.58,0:17:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,魏格納因此成為科學界的寵兒了嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So Wegener becomes the toast of the scientific world, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.45,0:17:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,並沒有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.42,0:17:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,大多數的地質學家嘲笑他的大陸漂移猜想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most geologists ridiculed Wegener's hypothesis of continental drift.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.83,0:17:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,他們更傾向於用他們的天然陸地連接理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They preferred their imaginary natural land bridges
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.80,0:17:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,對魏格納提出的證據作出解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to explain away Wegener's evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.70,0:17:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他們質疑大陸怎麼可能會破開海床堅硬的岩石呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How, they asked, could a continent plow through the solid rock of the ocean floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.81,0:17:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,魏格納並沒有令人信服的答案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wegener had no convincing answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.71,0:17:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,他成了這個領域的笑柄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He became the laughingstock of the field;
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.84,0:17:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,學術會議中的棄兒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a pariah at scientific conferences.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.98,0:17:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,儘管如此 魏格納依然堅持他的理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Despite this, Wegener continued to fight for his ideas,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.45,0:17:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,為了收集證據進行大膽的科學研究考察\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}conducting daring research expeditions to gather evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.82,0:17:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,其中又一次 他得知同事們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On one of these, he learned that colleagues were
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.66,0:18:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,被困在冰冠中 沒有食物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}trapped on an ice cap without food.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.53,0:18:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,在他增援後的返回途中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On his way back from the mission,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.73,0:18:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,他迷失在了暴風雪中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he became lost in a blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.70,0:18:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,就在他50歲生日過後的一兩天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A day or two after his 50th birthday,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.54,0:18:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,他失蹤了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he disappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.87,0:18:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,他永遠不知道 他的觀點被證明是正確的 而他被視為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he would be vindicated and come to be viewed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.48,0:18:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,歷史上最偉大的地質學家之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as one of the greatest geologists in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.15,0:18:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,科學家也是人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Scientists are human.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.39,0:18:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,也有盲點和偏見\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We have our blind spots and prejudices.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.19,0:18:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,科學是一種機制 就是要掃除這些盲點和偏見\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Science is a mechanism designed to ferret them out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.09,0:18:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,問題是 我們並非一直忠誠於這個科學的核心價值\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Problem is, we aren't always faithful to the core values of science
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.33,0:18:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,瑪麗·薩普就深知其中的精髓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Few people knew this better than Marie Tharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.61,0:18:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,1952年 瑪麗耐心地忍受著地質系同事的輕視\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's 1952, and Marie is patiently enduring the slights of her fellow members of the geology department.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.35,0:18:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,她的地質學學位和數學專業並不被他們放在眼裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Her degrees in geology and mathematics count for little with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.22,0:19:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,布魯斯·希森 一位愛荷華州來的研究生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Bruce Heezen, a graduate student from Iowa,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.39,0:19:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,剛剛結束了漫長的科考探險\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has just returned from a lengthy expedition
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.62,0:19:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,他們用聲納繪製海床圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to map the ocean floor using sonar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.30,0:19:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你能看看這些能用來做什麼吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Will you do something with these?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.37,0:19:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,布魯斯 你瞧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Bruce, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.11,0:19:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,一切都很明瞭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's-- it's all come together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.24,0:19:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,這條大裂谷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's this giant rift valley
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.08,0:19:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,貫穿整個大西洋底部\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that runs through the bottom of the Atlantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.11,0:19:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,得了吧 瑪麗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Aw, geez, Marie, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.31,0:19:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,又是這些廢話\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is just more girl talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.11,0:19:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你還沒受夠它們帶給你的麻煩嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You're not in enough trouble with everyone here already?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.78,0:19:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,這簡直就是大陸漂移理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This sounds too much like continental drift.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.75,0:19:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你想淪落到魏格納那樣嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You want to end up like Wegener?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.06,0:19:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但是瑪麗不為所動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Marie would not be dissuaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.99,0:19:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,多年後 瑪麗和布魯斯將一張海洋震央圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Years later, when Marie and Bruce placed a map of oceanic
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.90,0:19:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,放上看片台 蓋在她的海底地圖上時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}earthquake epicenters on a light table over her seafloor map,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.83,0:19:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,地震點遍佈整個大裂谷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the earthquakes fell right along the rift valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.90,0:19:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是魏格納漂移理論的確鑿證據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was the smoking gun for Wegener's moving continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.90,0:19:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}海底山脊的最高點
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.44,0:19:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,希森終於知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Heezen now knew
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.34,0:19:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,原來瑪麗一直都是對的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that Marie had been right all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.65,0:20:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他們共同繪製了第一張真正意義上的地球地圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Together, they created the first true map of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.52,0:20:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,包括了海底\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including the ocean floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.36,0:20:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,這使得我們終於可以開始解讀地球的自傳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We were at last ready to read the autobiography of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.42,0:20:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們乘坐想像之舟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let's take the Ship of the Imagination...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.09,0:20:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,進入對大部分人來說的都是深不可及的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to a part of the world that has been off-limits to all but a few of us
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.90,0:20:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的三分之二\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Two-thirds of the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.78,0:20:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,都處在1千英尺的水下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}lies beneath more than 1,000 feet of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.78,0:20:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}約300米左右
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.42,0:20:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,如此的廣闊 大部分都未經勘探\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a vast and largely unexplored frontier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.75,0:20:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,所有人都知道阿爾卑斯山脈和落基山脈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Everybody knows the Alps and the Rockies,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.32,0:20:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,但一些世界上最壯觀的山脈都被隱藏起來了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but some of the world's most amazing mountain ranges are hidden from view.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.80,0:21:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,當我們到達水面下1千米這個日光照射不到的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Below 1,000 meters, we enter a world where there is no sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.67,0:21:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,一個隱藏在黑暗中的神奇世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hidden in the darkness, a world of wonders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.44,0:21:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,這是世界上最長的海底山脈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the longest submarine mountain range in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.28,0:21:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,大西洋洋中脊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Atlantic Mid-Ocean Ridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.28,0:21:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}其橫跨大西洋及北冰洋 每年都以5至10厘米的速度向東西方向成長
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.52,0:21:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,它在我們的星球上形成一條宛如籃球接縫的線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It wraps around our globe like the seam on a baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.70,0:21:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,在過去 我們的星球與現在截然不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The past is another planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.56,0:21:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但是大多數人也不瞭解現在這個星球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but most of us don't really know this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.83,0:21:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,由於被水覆蓋 我們看不見這些山脈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We don't see the mountains for the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.50,0:21:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是瑪麗·薩普最初想像的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the world that Marie Tharp was the first to imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.07,0:21:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,山脊的最高峰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The highest peaks of the ridge
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.07,0:21:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,超出海底4千米\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}rise over four kilometers above the ocean floor
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.48,0:21:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,還有很多延綿的山脈和峽谷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are sprawling mountain ranges and canyons, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.41,0:21:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我們現在進入馬裏亞納海溝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We've now entered the Marianas Trench,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.41,0:21:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}海溝地處北太平洋西方海床\N海溝底部於海平面下之深度 遠勝珠穆朗瑪峰海平面上之高度
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.08,0:21:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上最深的峽谷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the deepest canyon on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.85,0:21:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,超過1萬米的深度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}more than ten kilometers deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.75,0:21:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,它形成構造力將海床推擠到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It formed when tectonic forces pushed the seabed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.72,0:22:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,相鄰的大陸板塊下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}under the adjoining continental plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.73,0:22:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,上過月球的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}More people have walked on the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.16,0:22:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,比下來這裏的多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than have ever been down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.76,0:22:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏的壓力達到了每平方英吋8噸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The pressure here is a crushing eight tons per square inch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.04,0:22:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,這樣的深度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Being this deep in the ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.24,0:22:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,就像是50架波音747疊在一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is like having 50 jumbo jets stacked on top of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.94,0:22:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,即使在這裏 也有生命的存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yet even here, life has taken hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.41,0:22:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,儘管陽光無法穿過這麼深的海水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The fact that sunlight can't penetrate the deep ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.85,0:22:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,但並不意味著這裏沒有光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}doesn't mean there isn't light down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.45,0:22:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,許多水下生物在暗中發光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Many underwater species glow in the dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.46,0:22:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我們稱之為生物螢光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}through a process called bioluminescence.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.53,0:22:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我們作為陸地上的哺乳動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our long history as land mammals,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.43,0:22:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,有著生活在陽光普照下的悠久歷史\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}denizens of the sunlit world, hasn't prepared us
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.60,0:22:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,使我們沒有像海底深處多種多樣的生物那樣的進化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the amazing variety of life that evolution has crafted in the deep oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.27,0:22:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,因為這裏沒有陽光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Since there's no sunlight down here,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.64,0:22:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,也就沒有光合作用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there's no photosynthesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.11,0:22:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,意味著沒有植物可供食用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That means there are no plants to feed on,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.22,0:23:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,可即使在這樣一個沒有陽光的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and yet, even here, in a world of permanent midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.62,0:23:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,也有一條繁榮的食物鏈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there's a thriving food chain.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.62,0:23:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,它由化學合成開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It begins with a process called chemosynthesis
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.43,0:23:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,這些只有顯微鏡下可見的生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These microscopic creatures have learned to eat
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.40,0:23:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,學會了食用那個孔裏出來的東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what's pouring out of that vent...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.10,0:23:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,一種被稱為硫化氫的有毒混合物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a noxious compound called hydrogen sulfide.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.17,0:23:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,那濃密的黑煙提供了化學能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That thick black smoke provides the chemical energy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.27,0:23:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,使得生命得以在此生存\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that makes life possible here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.44,0:23:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,小甲殼動物吃細菌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tiny crustaceans eat the bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.44,0:23:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,大一些的動物吃小甲殼動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the larger animals eat the crustaceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.32,0:23:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,地球未來的某一天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One day, on some future Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.82,0:23:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,這些山脈很有可能露出水面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}these mountains could very well end up above the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.82,0:23:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,構造作用力持續改變著地球的外貌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tectonic forces continue to shape our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.03,0:23:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,未來也會和現在截然不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The future is also another planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.00,0:23:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,以前 一個像這樣的火山\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was a volcano like this one
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.20,0:23:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,在數百萬年前 創造了夏威夷群島\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that created the Hawaiian islands millions of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.46,0:24:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我們住在一個沸騰大鍋的外殼上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We live on the crust of a seething cauldron.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.96,0:24:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的中心有一個大鐵芯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At the center of our planet, there's an iron core.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.03,0:24:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,它被包裹在一個液體的鐵殼內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's nested inside of a larger, liquid iron shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.87,0:24:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,再外層的部分稱之為地幔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wrapped over this is the part called the mantle.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.71,0:24:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,它是岩石構成 卻很熱很黏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's rocky but hot and viscous.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.64,0:24:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,就像是爐子上的一鍋濃湯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like a pot of soup cooking on a stove,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.15,0:24:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,不斷地翻騰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the mantle is churning.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.38,0:24:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,是什麼使它翻騰呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What keeps it moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.42,0:24:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,兩樣東西 一個是地球形成時遺留的高溫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Two things... the heat left over from Earth's formation,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.32,0:24:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,另一個就是地核中放射性物質的衰變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the decay of radioactive elements in the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.99,0:24:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,而這個外層 地殼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And this outer layer-- the crust,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.59,0:24:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你 我 大家所生活的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where you and me and everyone we know lives--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.66,0:24:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,厚度卻只相當於蘋果皮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is only as thick as the skin on an apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.24,0:24:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,地幔拖動固體的覆蓋層一起移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The mantle drags the solid overlying crust along with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.20,0:25:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,冷峻堅硬的地殼並不隨其所願\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The crust resists because it's cool and rigid.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.91,0:25:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,久而久之 到達了臨界點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From time to time, it reaches the breaking point.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.18,0:25:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,到了那時 大地開始搖晃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When that happens, the Earth quakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.51,0:25:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,並不是有人不聽話要受到懲罰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's not because somebody misbehaved and is being punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.88,0:25:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,它只是自然法則控制下的隨機力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's due to random forces that are governed by the laws of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.19,0:25:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,因為我們生存的時間太短N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our sense of the stability of the Earth is an illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.53,0:25:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,造成了我們對於地球穩定感的幻覺\\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}due to the shortness of our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.73,0:25:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們可以用地球本身的時間刻度觀察\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we could watch our planet on its own timescale,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.63,0:25:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,重大的變化要用上百萬年的時間才可以顯現出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in which big changes take millions of years to play out,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.27,0:25:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,那時我們才可以看出它是怎樣的一個動態有機體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we would see it as the dynamic organism it really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.15,0:25:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,這是三疊紀晚期時的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the world of the late Triassic period
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.65,0:25:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,距離現今約2億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about 200 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.82,0:25:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,那個小傢伙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That little guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.95,0:25:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,是我們的遠古祖先之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's one of our distant ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.42,0:25:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,它所在地方就是現在的新澤西州的紐瓦克\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He lived in Newark, New Jersey.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.63,0:26:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,不論你在地球上的什麼地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wherever you walk on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.83,0:26:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你的腳下都曾經有一個失落的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}lost worlds lie buried beneath your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.84,0:26:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,5千萬到1億年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}50 or 100 million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.07,0:26:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分貌似平常的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even the most seemingly ordinary places
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.57,0:26:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,都經歷了史詩般的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have been the scene of epic change.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.28,0:26:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,這些巖壁就是盤古大陸分裂的紀念碑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These Palisades are a monument to the breakup of the supercontinent Pangaea.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.92,0:26:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,連續的火山噴發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The sequence of volcanic eruptions
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.08,0:26:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,使這些懸崖導致了另一場大滅絕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that made these cliffs also led to the next mass extinction--
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.46,0:26:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,這場大滅絕宣告了三疊紀的終結\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the one that ended the Triassic world.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.59,0:26:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,但是造成一個物種滅絕的大災難\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But a catastrophic extinction event for one species
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.26,0:26:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,卻是另一個物種的寶貴機遇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a golden opportunity for another.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.67,0:26:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,三疊紀的物種滅絕給了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Triassic extinctions offered one group
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.10,0:26:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,另一個物種登上世界舞台中心的機會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that had been around for a while the chance to take center stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.71,0:26:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,恐龍們愉快茁壯地生活了大約1.7億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The dinosaurs had a good, long run for 170 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.15,0:26:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那時 印度還是一個島\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Back then, India was an island.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.99,0:26:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,每年向北方慢慢爬行幾英吋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It crept northward at the pace of a few inches per year
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.69,0:27:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,雖然緩慢的 但也無法阻擋它向亞洲靠攏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on its slow but inexorable rendezvous with Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.53,0:27:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,然後 再一次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Then, once again,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.63,0:27:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,地表下的熔岩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the molten rock beneath Earth's surface
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.13,0:27:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,噴射而出並且淹沒了印度西部的大部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}burst forth and flooded a huge area of western India.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.71,0:27:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,致命的一擊從天而降\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The knockout punch literally came out of the blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.38,0:28:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,一些幾百磅重的動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Few animals larger than a hundred pounds
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.75,0:28:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,從白堊紀晚期的大災難中倖存下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}survived the catastrophes of the late Cretaceous.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.82,0:28:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,塵埃雲帶來長達數月的寒冷黑夜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The dust cloud brought night and cold to the surface for months.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.16,0:28:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,恐龍因飢寒交迫而死\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The dinosaurs froze and starved to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.43,0:28:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,但還有一些在地下躲避的小動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there were small creatures who took shelter in the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.43,0:28:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,等它們再次出現時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And when they emerged...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.37,0:28:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,它們發現以前的獵食它們 威脅它們的惡霸都不見了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they found that the monsters who had hunted and terrorized them were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.90,0:28:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,地球變成了哺乳動物的天下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Earth was becoming the Planet of the Mammals.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.71,0:28:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,地球繼續不斷變化著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the Earth continued its ceaseless changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.61,0:28:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏曾是寸草不生的荒漠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was once a desert where nothing could grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.78,0:28:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,只有1百萬平方英里的沙和鹽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was a million square miles of sand and salt,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.52,0:28:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,比現在地球上任何環境都要惡劣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}far more hostile than any environment on Earth today.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.89,0:28:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,白天溫度高的可以烤麵包\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Daytime temperatures were hot enough to bake bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.46,0:28:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,因為它處在海面之下1英里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it was more than a mile below sea level,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.13,0:28:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,因此大氣壓比現在高出50%\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so the atmospheric pressure was about 50% higher than what we're used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.53,0:29:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,很難想出還有什麼環境比這更令人絕望\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It would be hard to think of a more unpromising environment on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.11,0:29:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,在5百50萬年前 在變成海之前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yet this was the basin of the Mediterranean five and a half million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.41,0:29:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏曾是地中海盆地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before it became a sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.61,0:29:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,地球平靜的時間總是短暫的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Earth never stops moving for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.58,0:29:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,大盆地西端的天然大水壩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The natural dam at the western end of the deep basin
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.72,0:29:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,倒塌了 可能是因為地震\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}gave way, probably due to earthquakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.39,0:29:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,洪災來了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the deluge began.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.93,0:29:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,兇猛的洪水規模甚至超過了尼加拉瓜大瀑布4萬倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The torrential waters rushed in at a rate 40,000 times greater than Niagara Falls,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.76,0:29:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,在不到一年的時間裏就將這遼闊的荒漠變成了地中海\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}turning a vast desert into the Mediterranean Sea... in less than a year
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.57,0:29:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,那時候人類還沒有出現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There were as yet no humans
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.74,0:29:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,無法目睹著壯麗的大洪水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to witness this enormous flood,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.98,0:29:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,也無法感嘆它創造的美景\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}nor to admire the beauty it created.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.78,0:29:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,與此同時 地球的另一端\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Meanwhile, half a world away,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.18,0:29:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,分開南北美洲的寬闊海峽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a broad channel separated North and South America...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.95,0:29:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,使洋流可以從大西洋流入太平洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}allowing ocean currents to flow from the Atlantic into the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.82,0:29:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,最終因構造作用力逐漸將兩塊大陸集合在一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tectonic forces gradually brought these two continents together
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.55,0:30:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,閉合了海峽並創造了巴拿馬地峽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}closing the channel and creating the Isthmus of Panama.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.03,0:30:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,這重塑了全球洋流模式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This reorganized the worldwide pattern of ocean currents,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.30,0:30:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,從而改變了全球的氣候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which, in turn, affected the global climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.81,0:30:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,茂盛綠色森林覆蓋的非洲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In Africa, the lush green forest canopy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.71,0:30:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,蛻變成了一片荒蕪\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}gave way to a sparser landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.11,0:30:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,一些專門生活在樹上的物種滅絕了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some species that were highly specialized for life in the trees became extinct
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.52,0:30:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,但一些多面手們卻可以\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the generalists, the ones that could find a way
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.46,0:30:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,找到一條生存之道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to make a living no matter what life threw at them,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.79,0:30:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是 忍耐 然後進化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}endured and evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.56,0:30:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的遠古祖先曾經為了躲避地面的掠食者而藏身於地底深處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our ancestors had once burrowed deep in the ground to avoid predators who stalked the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.54,0:30:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,當恐龍滅亡後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But when the dinosaurs perished,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.84,0:30:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,它們重獲天日\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they emerged into the daylight,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.67,0:30:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,無數年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and over the eons, made new lives
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.58,0:30:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,又爬回樹上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the branches of the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.64,0:30:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,它們發育出適合抓握的拇指和腳趾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They developed opposable thumbs and toes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.21,0:30:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,可以在樹枝間搖蕩 穿過寬闊的樹冠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for swinging from branch to branch, across the broad canopy of treetops,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.72,0:30:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,從而滿足它們所有的需求\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where all their needs were fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.99,0:30:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,它們也可以短暫的直立行走\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They could also walk upright, but only for short distances.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.76,0:31:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,周圍樹這麼多 它們也不需要走很遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With so many trees around, they didn't have to go very far.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.39,0:31:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,直到後來 氣溫下降 樹變得稀疏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But then it got colder, and the trees thinned out,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.20,0:31:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,遼闊的草原涌現出來 我們的祖先\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}broad grasslands sprang up, and our ancestors
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.87,0:31:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,被迫穿過草原尋找食物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were forced to traverse them in search of food.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.67,0:31:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,在熱帶大草原上 這就需要一套完全不同的技巧了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You needed a totally different skill set to make it on the savanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.54,0:31:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,以前 可以悠閒地坐在樹枝上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the old days, you could sit perched on your tree branch
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.04,0:31:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,遠遠地就能看到大型貓科動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and watch the big cats from a safe distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.51,0:31:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 優勢不復存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now you were playing on the same dangerous field.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.59,0:31:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,倖存者都是一些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The survivors were those who evolved the ability
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.26,0:31:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,可以用後肢長距離行走 並且能在必要時奔跑的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to walk great distances on their hind legs and to run when necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.29,0:31:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,這改變了它們觀察世界的方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This changed the way they looked at the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.46,0:31:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,行走時不再必須要有手和胳膊的幫助\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hands and arms were no longer tied up with walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.70,0:31:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,它們可以自由的收集食物 拾取樹枝和骨頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They were free to gather food and pick up sticks and bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.90,0:31:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,用來製造武器和工具\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These could be used as weapons and tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.47,0:31:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,想想看\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.31,0:31:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,一小塊土地上的地形變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A change in the topography of a small piece of land
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.91,0:31:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,再加上地球另一端的洋流變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}half a world away reroutes ocean currents.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.22,0:32:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,使得非洲變得更冷更乾燥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Africa grows colder and drier.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.59,0:32:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,大多數的樹無法適應新的氣候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of the trees can't withstand the new climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.49,0:32:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,生活在其中的靈長類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The primates who lived in them
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.59,0:32:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,必須要尋找新的家園 不知不覺中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have to seek other homes, and before you know it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.76,0:32:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,它們使用工具開始改造這個星球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they're using tools to remake the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.80,0:32:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,地球改變了人類的命運\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Earth has shaped the course of human destiny,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.67,0:32:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,還有遙遠世界的看不見的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but so has the invisible pull of distant worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.67,0:32:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,行星們影響著我們的生活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The planets have influenced our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.34,0:32:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,不是你想的那個意思\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but not in the way you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.87,0:32:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,金星的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The gravitational pull of Venus--
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.91,0:32:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,不強卻很近\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}small but close--
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.45,0:33:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,木星的引力雖遠卻很強\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and that of Jupiter-- distant but massive--
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.08,0:33:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,將地球的軸心拉向一側 一會這邊一會那邊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}tilted the Earth's axis this way and that...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.86,0:33:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,並且細微地扭曲了它的軌道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and ever so slightly tweaked the shape of its orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.86,0:33:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,這也週期性地改變了陽光照射在北部冰冠的數量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This periodically altered the amount of sunlight falling on the edge of the northern ice cap.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.27,0:33:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,有時使那裏的夏天更冷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sometimes it made the summers there colder,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.71,0:33:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,並使冰川向南移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the glaciers advanced southward
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.48,0:33:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,年復一年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from one year to the next,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.28,0:33:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,碾壓而過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}grinding and scraping,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.74,0:33:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,摧毀沿途的一切\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and crushing everything in their path.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.38,0:33:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是我們說的冰河時期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's what we call an ice age.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.55,0:33:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,而另一時間 地球軸心和軌道的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At other times, changes in Earth's axis and orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.79,0:33:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,使北極的夏天更熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}made the Arctic summers warmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.33,0:33:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,並使冰川融化 向後退縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the melting glaciers began to retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.33,0:33:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,想像一下我們的祖先要有多大的本事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Imagine how resourceful our ancestors had to be
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.07,0:33:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,才能在這種氣候的巨變中倖存下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in order to survive these radical changes in climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.17,0:33:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,每個冰河時期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With each glacial period,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.10,0:33:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,冰原都在侵蝕著海洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the ice sheets grow at the expense of the oceans;
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.17,0:34:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,海平面下降超過400英尺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the world sea level falls by more than 400 feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.17,0:34:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}約122米
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.58,0:34:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,沿著大陸的邊緣 使其露出大量的陸地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}uncovering wide areas of land along the edges of the continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.68,0:34:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,在1.5萬到2.5萬年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}15,000 to 25,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.02,0:34:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,有過一次冰原後縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there was a period when the ice receded,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.32,0:34:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,暫時露出了一段連接的陸地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}exposing a temporary land bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.79,0:34:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,通向地球另一半的大門緩緩開啟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The gateway to the other half of the planet swings open.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.19,0:34:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,成群結隊的流浪者通過連接的陸地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Bands of wanderers crossed the land bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.93,0:34:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,來到北美洲 有些去了南美洲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to North America and parts south.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.66,0:34:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,大約1萬年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}About 10,000 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.73,0:34:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,氣候和海平面的反覆變化停止了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the manic swings of the climate and sea levels came to a stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.44,0:34:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,一場新的更溫和的氣候時期到來了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A new and gentler climate age began.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.14,0:34:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,就是我們現在生活的時期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's the one we live in now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.21,0:34:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,當巨大的冰原融化時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When the great ice sheets melted,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.11,0:34:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,海水升到現在的高度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the sea rose to its present height
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.28,0:34:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,河水攜帶高地而來的泥沙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the rivers carried silt from the highlands
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.69,0:34:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,在流入大海時形成了河口沖積平原\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to build great delta plains where they met the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.19,0:34:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,在那些富饒的平原上 我們學會了全新的生活方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On those fertile plains, we learned a new way of life...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.03,0:34:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,如何種植食物以解決飢餓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how to grow things, to feed ourselves and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.06,0:34:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,對大部分人來說 這意味著一百萬年的遊蕩結束了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For most of us, this meant an end to a million years of wandering.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.74,0:35:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,行星間的相互吸引\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The way the planets tug at each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.87,0:35:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,地球表面的移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the way the skin of the Earth moves,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.14,0:35:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,這些運動對於氣候的影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the way those motions affect climate
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.51,0:35:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,對於生命和智力進化的影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the evolution of life and intelligence
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.35,0:35:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,它們集合在一起 使我們可以將\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they all combined to give us the means
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.08,0:35:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,河口沖積平原的淤泥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to turn the mud of those river deltas
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.35,0:35:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,轉變為最初的文明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the first civilizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.92,0:35:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,間冰期是獨一無二的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's nothing like an interglacial period,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.26,0:35:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,冰河時期中的一段溫暖舒適的間歇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one of those balmy intermissions in an ice age.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.23,0:35:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,好消息是這個時期 還將會持續\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the great news is that this one is due to last
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.70,0:35:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,5萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for another 50,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.87,0:35:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以鬆口氣了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What a break for our kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.11,0:35:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一個問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just one problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.61,0:35:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我們貌似不停的消耗這些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We can't seem to stop burning up all those
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.58,0:35:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,從石炭紀就深埋地下的樹木\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}buried trees from way back in the Carboniferous Age,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.11,0:35:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,它們已經是煤炭了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the form of coal;
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.58,0:35:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,還有古代浮游生物的遺骸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the remains of ancient plankton,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.05,0:35:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,現在是石油和天然氣了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the form of oil and gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.86,0:35:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,如果可以停止 氣候上來說 我們就脫離危險了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we could, we'd be home free, climate-wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.86,0:36:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,然而 我們向空氣中排放二氧化碳的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Instead, we're dumping carbon dioxide into the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.46,0:36:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,是自過去那場導致大滅絕的災難以來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at a rate the Earth hasn't seen since the great climate catastrophes of the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.80,0:36:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,前所未有的快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the ones that led to mass extinctions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.54,0:36:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我們好像無法戒除我們對這些燃料的迷戀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We just can't seem to break our addiction to the kinds of fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.14,0:36:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有意識到這將會把我們帶回恐龍時代的氣候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that'll bring back a climate last seen by the dinosaurs;
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.88,0:36:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,在那種氣候下 我們的沿海城市會被淹沒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a climate that will drown our coastal cities and wreak havoc
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.25,0:36:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,同時也會嚴重破壞我們的壞境和影響我們的食物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the environment and our ability to feed ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.22,0:36:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,一直以來 壯麗的太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All the while, the glorious sun
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.12,0:36:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,灑下潔淨 免費的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}pours immaculate, free energy down upon us;
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.16,0:36:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,遠遠超過我們的需要\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}more than we will ever need.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.00,0:36:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我們為什麼不能學習\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why can't we summon the ingenuity and courage
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.77,0:36:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,古人的智慧和勇氣呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the generations that came before us?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.07,0:36:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,既然恐龍們沒有預見到小行星的來臨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The dinosaurs never saw that asteroid coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.94,0:36:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼我們還不會引前車之鑒呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What's our excuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.18,0:36:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,有一條走廊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's a corridor
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.92,0:36:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,就在滅絕紀念堂內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the Halls of Extinction that is, right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.19,0:37:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,依然空空蕩蕩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}empty and unmarked.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.46,0:37:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的自傳依舊繼續書寫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The autobiography of the Earth is still being written.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.19,0:37:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,有可能我們的故事就在此終結\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's a chance that the end of our story lies in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.36,0:37:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,恭喜你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.30,0:37:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你還活著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.50,0:37:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,一條不間斷的線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's an unbroken thread that stretches across
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.31,0:37:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,綿延跨越30億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}more than three billion years
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.71,0:37:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,將我們與這個世界上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that connects us to the first life
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.68,0:37:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,第一個生命聯繫起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that ever touched this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.88,0:37:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,想想我們無數的遠古祖先有多麼的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think of how tough, resourceful and lucky
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.28,0:37:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,堅強 聰明 和幸運\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all of our countless ancestors must have been
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.55,0:37:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,生存至今\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to survive long enough
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.42,0:37:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,將生命的信息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to pass on the message of life to the next
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.66,0:37:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,一代又一代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the next...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.06,0:37:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,繼續接著一代又一代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the next generation,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.60,0:37:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,一直代代相傳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hundreds of millions of times...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.91,0:38:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,傳到我們這一代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before it came to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.58,0:38:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,需要跨過多少河流\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There were so many rivers to cross,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.91,0:38:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,期間還有無數的障礙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so many hazards along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.52,0:38:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,獵食者 饑荒 疾病\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Predators, starvation, disease,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.65,0:38:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,對形勢的誤判 漫長的寒冬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}miscalculation, long winters,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.82,0:38:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,旱災 洪災 暴力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}drought, flood and violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.96,0:38:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,還有偶爾從地下噴發的火山\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not to mention the occasional upheavals that erupted from within our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.88,0:38:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,和天上落下的末日天體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the apocalyptic bolts that come from the blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.05,0:38:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,無論從我們起源何處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No matter where we hail from
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.97,0:38:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的祖先是誰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or who our parents were, we are descended
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.10,0:38:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我們都是不可思議的大災難的倖存者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the hearty survivors of unimaginable catastrophes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.27,0:38:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,每個人都是在最漫長最危險的接力賽中的參賽者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each of us is a runner in the longest and most dangerous relay race there ever was,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.68,0:38:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,此時此刻 接力棒就在我們的手中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and at this moment, we hold the baton in our hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.55,0:38:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,過去是截然不同的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The past is another planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.89,0:38:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,未來將是如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And so is the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.43,0:38:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,大約2.5億年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some 250 million years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.97,0:39:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,許多地質學家認為地球上的陸地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}many geologists think that the lands of the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.17,0:39:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,會再次聚合在一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will be united once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.28,0:39:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,這些美景將不復存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All this beauty will have vanished
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.42,0:39:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我們此時的地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the Earth of our moment in time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.56,0:39:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,就變成了那時的失落世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will take its place among the lost worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.63,0:39:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,板塊構造的偉大內部動力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The great internal engine of plate tectonics
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.30,0:39:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,對生命漠不關心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is indifferent to life,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.33,0:39:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,就如同地球軌道和軸心的細微變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as are the small changes in the Earth's orbit and tilt
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.27,0:39:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,還有偶爾來自小天體的撞擊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the occasional collisions with little worlds on rogue orbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.31,0:39:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,這些活動對於我們星球表面幾十億年裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These processes have no notion of what has been going on
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.28,0:39:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,發生的事情完全沒有概念\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}over billions of years on our planet's surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.81,0:39:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,它們不在乎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They do not care.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.85,0:39:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,每個人都只是這顆小行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each of us is a tiny being
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.02,0:39:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,外殼上的乘客\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}riding on the outermost skin of one of the smaller planets
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.79,0:39:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,繞著自己的恆星走上幾十圈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a few dozen trips around the local star.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.82,0:40:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上最古老的生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The things that live the longest on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.46,0:40:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,也只不過堅持了地球年齡的百萬分之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}endure for only about a millionth of the age of our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.53,0:40:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,當然 任何一個有機體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So, of course, the individual organisms
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.60,0:40:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,是不可能看到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}see nothing of the overall pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.14,0:40:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,大陸變化的全貌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Of changing continents...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.17,0:40:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,氣候變化的全貌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}climate...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.68,0:40:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,進化的全貌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.71,0:40:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我們明白 我們的小小起源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That we understand even a little of our origins
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.68,0:40:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,都是人類洞察和勇氣的偉大勝利之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is one of the great triumphs of human insight and courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.95,0:40:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我們是誰 我們怎麼來到這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Who we are and why we are here can only be glimpsed
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.72,0:40:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,答案只能通過拼湊零星的碎片獲得\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by piecing together something of the full picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.66,0:40:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,完整的答案必然包含無數的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which must encompass eons of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.66,0:40:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,幾百萬種物種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}millions of species...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.57,0:40:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一大批的不同天體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and a multitude of worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.14,0:40:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,以這個角度看也不用感到奇怪\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In this perspective, it's not surprising
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.00,0:40:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,那是因為我們本身就是一個謎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we're a mystery to ourselves and that,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.15,0:40:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,儘管我們很自豪\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}despite our manifest pretension,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.59,0:41:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但我們還不是這個小星球上的主人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we are far from being masters of our own little house.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.56,0:41:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,這條走廊入口還沒有代表它的紀元的名稱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This new corridor has no name above the entrance to designate its epoch, and we don't yet know
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.47,0:41:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,也還不知道哪個滅亡的物種會被掛在牆上作為紀念\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which failed species will be memorialized within its walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.84,0:41:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,現在發生的一切 有無數的可能 可大可小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What happens here, in countless ways, both large and small,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.54,0:41:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,而這一切都取決於我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is being written by us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.91,0:41:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,現在的我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Right now.
